[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a pretty normal preemptive 3\D bid.

SOUTH has the equivalent of an opening 1NT bid and will be very tempted to bid 3NT.

That might turn out to be a disaster, particularly if SOUTH is unable to reach the NORTH hand.

SOUTH should assume NORTH can win six tricks if 
\Ds are trumps. Thinking this way points SOUTH to her 
best call - PASS.}

